itemLabel: A. V. Alexander, 1st Earl Alexander of Hillsborough

wikipedia_page.main: Albert Victor Alexander, 1st Earl Alexander of Hillsborough,  (1 May 1885 – 11 January 1965), was a British Labour and Co-operative politician. He was three times First Lord of the Admiralty, including during the Second World War, and then Minister of Defence under Clement Attlee.
